they're hundreds of years old,

10:01.167 --> 10:02.400
they do...
[Groans]

10:02.402 --> 10:04.302
...shave their -- When
you say it out loud, I mean...

10:04.304 --> 10:06.838
[Telephone ringing]
Ah.

10:06.840 --> 10:10.575
I-It's a show
about feelings.

10:11.378 --> 10:13.178
-Yeah?
-Stan, it's Kevin.

10:13.180 --> 10:14.479
I dig graves
down at the cemetery.

10:14.481 --> 10:16.914
I know who you are,
Kev-o.
Right. Okay.

10:16.916 --> 10:18.050
After you left,

10:18.052 --> 10:20.051
I went and checked out
all of Denise's old haunts --

10:20.053 --> 10:21.320
the abandoned car wash,

10:21.322 --> 10:23.988
that big pile of wigs
behind the church,

10:23.990 --> 10:25.057
the false teeth museum,

10:25.059 --> 10:27.926
the funeral home that's only
for circus people...

10:27.928 --> 10:29.861
Mirror:
[Whispering] Evie.

10:29.863 --> 10:33.264
♪♪

10:33.266 --> 10:34.633
...that building
with no windows

10:34.635 --> 10:35.734
where they make
old people sew,

10:35.736 --> 10:37.936
the record shop
that became a video rental

10:37.938 --> 10:39.738
that's now a phone store
that's closing,

10:39.740 --> 10:42.207
that bridge that
the goats are afraid of...

10:42.209 --> 10:44.409
Evie.

10:44.411 --> 10:46.611
Evie.

10:46.613 --> 10:48.113
[Portal whirring]

10:48.115 --> 10:50.682
...that homeless guy who has
a house he just won't go in.

10:53.420 --> 10:54.819
Hello?

10:54.821 --> 10:57.389
Hang on to your hat.
The phone store's clos--

10:59.159 --> 11:01.093
Oh, hell, not again.

11:01.095 --> 11:03.762
♪♪

11:03.764 --> 11:06.431
[Indistinct conversations,
dog barking]

11:06.433 --> 11:09.901
Lookin' good, Crazy Ray.
Lookin' good.

11:09.903 --> 11:13.237
Okay, you kill a hobo,
and I'll drink his blood.

11:13.239 --> 11:15.907
Denise: Zach, why can't you
do this again?

11:15.909 --> 11:17.042
